## Supported formats

Buttondown accepts PNG, JPG, and GIF images. SVG files are rejected by default because most email clients don't render them reliably â€” your subscribers would see a broken image instead.

If you upload an SVG, the API will return a `400` with:

```json
{
  "detail": "SVG files are not supported. Please upload a PNG, JPG, or GIF."
}
```

### Bypassing SVG validation

If you know what you're doing (e.g. your SVGs are only used on the web archive, not in emails), you can bypass this restriction by providing a `X-Buttondown-Live-Dangerously` header with a value of `true`:

```bash
curl -X POST "https://api.buttondown.com/v1/images" \
  -H "Authorization: Token YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -H "X-Buttondown-Live-Dangerously: true" \
  -F "image=@logo.svg"
```
